menu "Mining"

config MINING_PIN_HOTLOOP_DATA
    bool "Pin mining hot-loop data to cache-aligned static storage"
    default y
    help
      Place the per-nonce mining hot-loop data (block2 and the HW SHA backend
      context) in cache-line-aligned static (BSS) storage instead of on the
      stack. Pinning isolates these on fixed D-cache lines, protecting the hot
      loop from layout shifts caused by future feature additions (TA-392), and
      benefits boards with a larger per-nonce working set (ESP32-S3 / AHB SHA).

      Disable on ESP32-D0 (classic WROOM-32): after the TA-396 early-reject
      byte-order fix its reject-path working set is tiny, and stack placement
      measured ~1.5% faster than the aligned static (445 -> 452 kH/s).

endmenu
